main event: An unidentified object was sighted entering the atmosphere over the Pacific Ocean on February 9, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting was confirmed by Aloha Airlines Aircraft 731,The object was observed at a 45-degree elevation and moved at high speed,The object burned out at 30 degrees above the horizon,The observation lasted for approximately 3 minutes,The report categorized the object as a probable meteor sighting.
sighted object: a brilliant white object entering the atmosphere
